<HEADLINE> Pakistan Pledges Support for Palestinian Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has been a firm
supporter of the Palestinian cause since the latter's birth and
would continue to support its Palestinian brothers, Speaker of
Pakistan's National Assembly Illahi Bakhsh Soomro said here today.
</P>
<P>
The speaker made the remarks while meeting Palestinian
Ambassador to Pakistan Ahmed Razzaq El Salman, who briefed him on
the political situation in Palestine and the Middle East and
underlined the need for closer collaboration between the
Palestinian and Pakistani parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Soomro agreed that there should more interaction between the
two parliaments and said Pakistan has already been supporting all
the Palestinian issues in world parliamentary bodies.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to support any issue raised by our Palestinian
brethren," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian ambassador expressed his thanks for Pakistan's
unswerving support for the Palestinian cause.  
</P>
</TEXT>
