<HEADLINE> Ethiopian FM to Visit S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Foreign Minister
Seyoun Mesfin is scheduled to start his six-day South African
tour tomorrow, the Department of Foreign Affairs announced today.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of the visit is to identify areas of bilateral
trade and socio-political relations," said a statement issued by
the department in the capital Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
A declaration of intent, a memorandum of understanding on
cooperation in agriculture and an air services agreement are
expected to be signed in Cape Town during Mesfin's visit.
</P>
<P>
"The visit is significant as it will be the first official
visit to South Africa by a senior government representative from
Ethiopia," said the statement. 
