<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Girls Commit Suicide Defying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Six local Afari girls have
recently committed suicide in Ethiopia's northern Afar Region
defying "abusuma", a traditional marriage imposed on them against
their will.
</P>
<P>
Local people in the neighborhood said the girls shot, hanged
and threw themselves into rivers in a desperate act against
marriage with their cousins.
</P>
<P>
They said the number of young women fighting against
traditional marriage, most of them around 15 years of age, is on
the rise as they prefer death to being the spouses of old men of
80 years of age or even above.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government said "abusuma" violates women's
rights, urging pertinent bodies to bring about behavioral changes
in local communities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
