<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cook Unveils British Foreign Policy Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's new Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook unveiled here today the new Labor government's foreign
policy strategy, promising to make Britain a leading player in the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference launching the document, Cook set
out a series of priorities in a "Mission Statement", saying "New
Labor is determined to bring businesslike approach to the
Government and make Britain a leading player in a Europe of
independent nation states."
</P>
<P>
Cook, who has promised to make a new start with Britain's EU
partners, said that the British government will work for agreement
on the Inter Governmental Conference (IGC) conclusions, while
"resolutely defending British interests."
</P>
<P>
On Britain's six-month EU presidency next year, Cook said: "Our
two main objectives for the British presidency will be to remove
the remaining barriers to trade within the single market and to
get talks on (EU) enlargement off to a flying start."
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Secretary pointed out that the country's security
"will remain based on the North Atlantic Alliance."
</P>
<P>
"We must manage the enlargement of NATO to ensure that a wider
alliance is also a stronger alliance and that the process reduces
rather increases tensions between East and West," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pledging to enhance British prosperity, Cook said that the
Labor government will "make it a top priority for our network of
overseas posts to promote British exports and boost British jobs."
</P>
<P>
On the Europe-Asia summit to be held in London next April, Cook
expressed his conviction that the British government "will work
for enhanced dialogue and specific measures of cooperation,
including trade, investment and technology transfer."
</P>
<P>
Other priorities outlined in Cook's statement include
strengthening the Commonwealth, securing reform of a more
effective United Nations and protection of global environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
