<HEADLINE> Anti-Mine Conference to Be Held in Johannesburg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 12 (Xinhua) --An anti-mine confernce will be
held here next week at which Landmine experts from across Africa
will make recommendations for consideration by a summit meeting
of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) in June this year.
</P>
<P>
The planned three-day conference, scheduled to take place at
the World Trade Centre in eastern suburbs of Johannesburg from
May 19 to 21, is to be organised by the OAU in cooperation with
the South African government, said the OAU in a statement
issued in pretoria today.
</P>
<P>
"This conference is part of the Ottawa process to achieve a
global ban on the use, development, production, stockpiling and
transfer of anti-personal landmines by the end of the year," said
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The conference is aimed to provide a common African forum to
support the process towards a global ban on anti-personal mines,
while improving African cooperation in mine clearance and
providing assistance to landmine victims.
</P>
<P>
It will also appeal to the international community to increase
its assistance to African countries, the world's most affected
continent in this respece, the statement added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
