<HEADLINE> 36 Percent of EU Electricity from Nuclear Power Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 12 (Xinhua) -- About 36 percent of power supply in
the European Union (EU) states was generated by nuclear power
plants in 1996, a survey published today in Frankfurt showed.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey conducted by the Federation of German
Nuclear Power Plants (VDEW), the share of nuclear energy in the
total power supply in the EU states grew by one percent in 1996
compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
With 77 percent of its power supply covered by nuclear energy,
France remained the front-runer among the EU countries. Germany
was below the EU average with a nuclear energy share of 30
percent, followed by Finland with 27 percent and Britain with 26
percent.
</P>
<P>
Only five percent of power supply in the Netherlands was
produced by nuclear power plants, the survey said. Seven of the 15
EU states do not generate nuclear power.  
</P>
</TEXT>
