<HEADLINE> Rape Cases Rise in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 12 (Xinhua) -- There has been a steady rise in the
number of reported rape cases in Zimbabwe with a total 3,012
cases being reported last year, Zimbabwean Deputy Police
Commissioner Godwin Matanga said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing some 45 police officers from nine provinces
attending a Zimbabwean republic police training seminar, Matanga
said the most disturbing aspect is that about 52 percent of the
cases involved assaults on children below the age of 16 years.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''Viewed in the light of the raging AIDS pandemic, it
is shattering to imagine what devastation this is having on our
adults of tomorrow.''
</P>
<P>
Accordling to Matanga, 2,315 rape cases were reported in
Zimbabwe in 1993, 2,610 in 1994 and 3,148 in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
