<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-12 16:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Forces, Lebanese Guerrillas Exchange Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli warplanes launched three
consecutive raids at suspected guerrilla targets in south
Lebanon this afternoon, following an attack by Lebanese
guerrillas on an Israeli position inside an Israeli-occupied
border strip.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in the Israeli self-proclaimed "security
zone" said that one Israeli soldier and four members of the
Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army militia were injured in the
morning attack.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Lebanese National News Agency (LNNA) said that
Israeli warplanes carried out today's first air raid at Iglim
Al-Toffah at 2:20 p.m. (1120 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Iglim Al-Toffah, which means province of apple, some 60
kilometers southeast of Beirut, is a ridge often used by
guerrillas as a springboard to attack the buffer zone set up
by Israel in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The warplanes fired two air-to-surface missiles at a target
located between the villages of Jebal Sejoud and Mazra Aqmata,
the LNNA said, adding that black smoke was witnessed rising high
over the area.
</P>
<P>
Before the air raid, Israeli warplanes had flied
reconnaissance missions over Iglim Al-Toffah, and Israeli
artillery bombarded the vicinities of Sejoud, Rihan and Mazra
Aqmata.
</P>
<P>
Around 2:50 p.m., several Israeli helicopters launched a
second air raid, firing one missile at Sejoud and sweeping the
same target with machinegun fire.
</P>
<P>
Ten minutes later, the helicopters flied back to Iglim
Al-Toffah and fired another missile and opened machineguns at
Mazra Aqmata.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of casualties in the air raids,
the LNNA said.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
announced that they attacked this morning an outpost of the
Israeli occupation forces opposite Sejoud this morning, "killing
and wounding a number of Israeli soldiers."
</P>
<P>
Security sources in the border strip confirmed that one
Israeli soldier and four SLA militiamen were injured in the
guerrilla offensive.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah, also
said that its militants bombarded the Israeli positions of Bir
Kalab and Kassara Aroush with mortar shells.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by guerrillas and retaliatory air raids
and bombardments by Israeli forces and their client militia
constitute a daily scene in south Lebanon, the last active
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Six Israeli soldiers have been killed and more than 35 others
wounded in fightings with Hezbollah guerrillas since this year.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish state established the 1,100-square-kilometer
"security zone" in 1985 ostensibly to protect northern Israel
from cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
