<HEADLINE> PTA Bank Launches Marketing Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Eastern and Southern African
Trade and Development Bank (PTA Bank) has embarked on an
aggressive marketing campaign to enhance the competitiveness of
exports among PTA member states.
</P>
<P>
The bank, which is the financial arm of the Common Market for
East and Southern Africa (COMESA ), said in its latest bulleting
that the strategy of the exercise hinged on raising cheaper funds
for exporters.
</P>
<P>
The bank had since structured and arraged a 50 million U.S.
Dollars facility from the U.S. to support exports in a member
country under this program.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin said trade finance is an area where the bank's
role is becoming more pronounced in the sub-region, and that this
had been a result of the small number of financial institutions
providing this service.
</P>
<P>
The PTA bank, which was established in 1985, provides various
types of trade financing to trading entities in member states
with priority being given to finance self-liquidating export
oriented transactions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President of the bank Martin Ogang is in Zimbabwe
to attend the institution's 13th annual general meeting which
began in Harare today. 
</P>
