<HEADLINE> Iranian Economic Minister Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Minister of Economic
Affairs and Finance Morteza Mohammad Khan arrived here today on a
four-day official visit during which he would discuss economic
cooperation with Kuwaiti.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Khan said talks during his visit would touch
aspects of economic, cultural and political cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti official sources the two sides would concluding
agreements on avoiding double taxation and the guarantee and
protection of investment between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The talks would also cover the completion of a giant
steel project between Iran and Kuwait although procedures still
need long time to finish, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Khan's visit to Kuwait is the third time that an Iranian
ministerial official came to Kuwait since the start of this
year. Iranian oil minister and foreign minister separately
visited Kuwait in February and March.
</P>
<P>
Khan's delegation includes a team representing the Iranian
Ministry of Minerals and other finance and trade officials.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Iran have expressed an ardent desire to
strengthen further their relations through exchanging delegations
in various fields since the Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti-Iranian relations have witnessed a remarkable
development during the recent years, especially since the
beginning of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The two way trade volume has increased from 120 million
U.S. dollars in 1991 to 400 million U.S. dollars in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
