<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Dar Es Salaam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived here from Yaounde this afternoon to start his official
good-will visit to Tanzania at the invitation of Tanzanian
President Benjamin Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
Li and his entourage were greeted at the airport by President
Mkapa, Vice-President Omar Ali Juma, Second Vice-President and
President of Zanzibar Salmin Amour, Prime Minister Fredrick
Tluway Sumaye, dozens of senior government officials and
high-ranking army officers, noted parliamentarians, as well as
diplomatic envoys of foreign countries in the capital and
representatives of international organizations in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
A warm and grand welcome ceremony was held at the airport upon
arrival in which Li Peng, in the accompany of President Mkapa,
reviewed the guards of honor of the three services of the army.
</P>
<P>
Along the 20-kilometer road from the airport to the Sheraton
Hotel, Li Peng, standing in an open car together with Mkapa, were
greeted and cheered by hundreds of thousands of local people. The
two leaders kept waving hands to them and the cheering of "warmly
welcome Chinese premier and our Chinese friends" in both Chinese
and English were heard every once in a while.
</P>
<P>
During Li Peng's stay here, he is scheduled to hold talks with
President Mkapa on further advancing the bilateral relations and
major international and regional issues of mutual interest and
meet with other Tanzanian leaders.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng's Tanzania trip is the last leg of his seven-nation
African tour which has already taken him to Seychelles, Zambia,
Mozambique, Gabon, Cameroun and Nigeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
