<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Beheads Nationals, Bahraini </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today beheaded
two nationals who were convicted of raping a married women.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Press Agency reported that a Saudi Interior Ministry
statement said Nasser Bin Muqbel Al-amri and Ahmad Bin Uweidh
Al-Sahli broke into the house of a Saudi National and raped his
wife earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The two culprits, each with a criminal record, also stole some
property from the house.
</P>
<P>
They were beheaded in the holy city of Al-Madina Al-Munawara
after they were convicted of the crime in a special court.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Bahraini citizen named Mohammad Aziz Hasrallah
was also beheaded in Saudi Arabia today on charge of smuggling
heroin inside his body to Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Rapists, murderers and drug dealers are considered serious
offenders in the Islamic kingdom and are usually beheaded with a
sword according to the Islamic Sharia law.
</P>
<P>
A total of 30 offenders have been beheaded in Saudi Arabia
since the beginning of this year on various crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
