<HEADLINE> French Presidential Spokeswoman on Chirac's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming visit by President
Jacques Chirac to China is aimed at establishing a long-term and
global partnership between France and China, and contributing to
the building of a multipolar and harmonious world in the 21st
century, said French presidential spokeswoman Catherine Colonna
today.
</P>
<P>
At a press briefing on the visit to be paid by President Chirac
to China from May 15 to 18, Colonna said that since China adopted
the policy of reform and opening, it has achieved great social and
economic development, and will become a first-rate world power in
the next few years.
</P>
<P>
She said that the return of China to the world stage is
changing the world balance of power, and will also be an important
element in the global strategic balance in the next century.
</P>
<P>
She pointed out that since France and China signed a joint
communique to fully normalize relations in 1994, bilateral
relations have been further developed.
</P>
<P>
France welcomes the return of China to the world stage, and is
willing to accompany China in the historic process of its
modernization, said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
She also recalled that France and China played their role in
opposing a bipolar world power structure during the era of
Chairman Mao Zedong and President Charles de Gaulle, and said that
they are playing their role in the establishment of a multipolar
world today.
</P>
