<HEADLINE> China, Nigeria Agree on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- China and Nigeria signed here today
four documents of bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and Nigerian Head of State
General Sani Abacha jointly presided over the signing ceremony
held in the state house in Abuja, capital of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The four documents included an agreement on investment
protection, a protocol on cooperation in a steel project, a
protocol on cooperation in power engineering construction and an
agreement on petroleum cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu
Yi, General Manager of China National Petroleum Corporation Zhou
Yongkang, Nigerian Minister of Industries Mohammed Haladu and
Nigerian Minister of Power and Steel Alhaji Dalhatu, signed the
documents.
</P>
<P>
The signing of the four documents marked new progress in
economic cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the two countries expressed optimism for the
prospects of Sino-Nigerian cooperation, based on equality and
mutual benefit. 
