<HEADLINE> Jet Lands at Wrong Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Officials with Continental
Airlines of the United States are investigating why one of their
flights mistakenly landed at an abandoned naval airfield instead
of Corpus Christi International Airport in Texas about four miles
away.
</P>
<P>
A Continental spokesman says the airline has not determined yet
why the pilot landed at the wrong place Sunday, and the crew was
expected to meet with airline investigators Monday, news reports
said.
</P>
