<HEADLINE> Turkish President Leaves for ECO Summit in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
left here today for Turkmenistan to attend the Economic
Cooperation Organization (ECO) summit to be held between May 13
and 14.
</P>
<P>
During the summit, Demirel will discuss with other leaders of
the ECO member states some issues of common concern, including
transportation of natural gas, telecommunications infrastructure
as well as communications cooperation.
</P>
