<HEADLINE> Croatia to Hold Presidential Election in Mid-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Croatian government today
decided to hold the country's presidential election on June 15 of
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Croatian election laws, the presidential election
should be held at least 30 days before the mandate of the
five-year presidency expires.
</P>
<P>
The last election, which was held on August 3, 1992, was won by
incumbent President Franjo Tudjman who is still the most popular
politician of the country according opinion polls.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman will stand for the election as the candidate of the
ruling Croatian Democratic Union, while of opposition parties,
only Vlado Gotovac of the Social Liberal Party has indicated that
he will run for the presidency. 
</P>
