<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, US Military Heads Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States will
step up contacts and dialogue between their armed forces as part
of the efforts to improve bilateral relations, senior Chinese and
US military officers said here today.
</P>
<P>
During the highest level military talks between the two
countries in over a decade this morning, the Chinese side
expressed the will to carry out contacts and dialogue between the
armed forces of the two countries in a well-planned and scheduled
way.
</P>
<P>
The contacts and dialogue should be conducted on the basis of
mutual benefit and mutual respect, Chief of General Staff of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army Fu Quanyou told John
Shalikashvili, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff of the United
States, during the talks in the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse.
</P>
<P>
Shalikashvili is the highest ranking US military officer who
has ever visited China since 1985. He arrived in Beijing on May 12
for an official good-will visit as Fu's guest.
</P>
<P>
During the friendly and frank talks, the two sides exchanged
views on the issues of the security situation of the Asia-Pacific
region, the defense, and foreign policies of their own countries
and bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that links between the two armed forces compose a
crucial component of the relationship between the two
countries. He also reviewed the improvement of the relations
between the two armed forces since Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of
China's Central Military Commission and minister of national
defense, visited the US last year.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed the arrangement of contacts between the
armed forces in the short term. They agreed to keep contact and
dialogue on the issues of US military vessels' berthing at Hong
Kong after July 1, 1997 and the avoidance of maritime accidents.
</P>
<P>
On the regional security situation, Fu pointed out that the
Asia-Pacific region enjoys relatively stable political situation
and sustained economic development. However, there are still some
factors of instability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China has already made positive contributions to
and will make fresh efforts for the development and stability of
the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970513.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, US Military Heads Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fu pointed out that China and the US are two important big
powers in the world. The Sino-US relations are one of the most
crucial bilateral relations in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China places great importance on its relations
with the US and has made unremitting efforts to promote the links.
</P>
<P>
Fu stressed that the Taiwan issue is the kernel question of the
bilateral relations. The Chinese side expects that the US side
will handle this issue in a proper way and strictly abide by the
three joint communiques signed by the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that the two countries are facing a good opportunity to
further improve and promote bilateral relations at present. He
said that the two sides should seize this opportunity.
</P>
<P>
In line with the principle of "enhancing trust, reducing
troubles, promoting cooperation, and avoiding confrontation" that
Chinese President Jiang Zemin put forward, Fu said, the two sides
should always take into consideration the common interest of the
two countries, stand at a greater height, be more far-sighted,
strictly abide by the principles of the three joint communiques,
and properly deal with some sensitive issues between them, so as
to further improve and develop the Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Shalikashvili praised the big changes that have happened in
China since he last visit the country over a decade ago. He said
that the US has significant political and economic interest in the
Asia-Pacific region, so that it wishes that the region will
maintain stability and development. He said that the US does not
want to contain anyone, especially not China. The US places great
importance on the development of relations with China, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the US upholds the "one China" policy, abides by
the three joint communiques signed by the two governments and will
not have any official links with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Shalikashvili expressed gladness over the recent contacts
between the armed forces of the two countries. He wishes that the
two armed forces will maintain contacts and further develop their
links.
</P>
<P>
Shalikashvili invited Fu to visit the US. Fu accepted the
invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
