<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, May 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA -- The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) today
condemned Monday's attack on its staff by five armed men in
military uniforms in the eastern Zairean town of Goma.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- A powerful earthquake measuring 6.1 on the open ended
Richter scale today rocked Japan's main southwestern island of
Kyushu this afternoon, injuring at least six people, the
Metereological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The 7th Arab Parliamentary Union (APU) Conference
opened here today, with a call to enhance Arab solidarity and
establish a powerful economic grouping.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian President Sali Berisha said Monday that
authority of the multinational force in Albania should not be
expanded. 
</P>
