<HEADLINE> URGENT: SAARC Vows to Create Free Trade Zone by 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KURUMBA, the Maldives, May 13 (Xinhua) -- South Asian leaders
have decided to move faster toward trade liberalization in their
region, pledging to create the South Asian Free Trade Area (SAFTA)
by the year 2001, four years ahead of a previous deadline.
</P>
<P>
Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral said here this evening
that leaders of the seven-member South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC), at their summit in the Maldives,
have chosen 2001 as the target year to establish the free trade
zone.
</P>
<P>
The leaders had earlier decided to set up SAFTA preferably by
the year 2000 but not later than 2005.  
</P>
