<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Shalikashvili </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A healthy, stable Sino-US
relationship is not only in the interests of the peoples of both
countries, but also beneficial for peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole, Chinese Defence
Minister Chi Haotian told John Shalikashvili, chairman of the
Joint Chiefs of Staff of the United States, here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also a vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission and a state councilor, met today with Shalikashvili,
the highest-ranking US military officer to visit China in more
than a decade.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse, Chi
reviewed the progress of contacts between the armed forces of the
two countries in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is the largest developing country, while the
US is the largest developed country in the world. Taking a healthy
and stable Sino-US relationship into the 21st century is not only
in the interests of the peoples of the two countries, but also
beneficial to maintaining peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific
region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that Shalikashvili's current visit to China
would further promote understanding and trust between the two
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Shalikashvili and his entourage on China's
reform and opening up and its defence-oriented military policy.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the passing away of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, a
great Chinese leader, the Chinese people have been united solidly
around the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China with
Jiang Zemin at the core. China will staunchly march along the road
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, which Deng
Xiaoping initiated.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China places great importance on the
development of relations with the US. He said that the two sides
should stick to the principles of "enhancing trust, reducing
troubles, promoting cooperation and avoiding confrontation" that
Chinese President Jiang Zemin has put forward.
</P>
<P>
They should strictly abide by the principles set out in the
three joint communiques signed by the two governments, proceed
from the common interests of the two countries and face the 21st
century so as to put Sino-US relations on a track of healthy and
stable development, Chi added.
</P>
<P>
Shalikashvili conveyed the greetings of US Secretary of Defence
William Cohen and former Secretary of Defence William Perry to
Chi. He also recalled the pleasant experience of Chi's visit to
the US last year.
</P>
<P>
He said that for a person who has not visited China for the
past decade, the changes in the country are "remarkable."
</P>
<P>
He said that the US is ready to push forward the contacts and
dialogue between the armed forces of the two countries, so as to
further improve and promote bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
