<HEADLINE> China Commends Outstanding Disabled Persons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government held a
meeting at the Great Hall of the People here today to commend
outstanding disabled persons and people who have helped the
disabled.
</P>
<P>
A preface written by president Jiang Zemin to a book titled
"Song of Self-Supporting" was read at the meeting. In it, Jiang
says that China has 60 million disabled people and they have
relations with one-fifth of all Chinese families. The country must
handle this social issue properly and must on no account dodge the
problem, he stresses.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, general secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee, adds that the issue is also related to the full
realization of human rights and the liberation of productivity.
</P>
<P>
According to the leader, humanitarianism is the yardstick for
dealing with the relations between people. The Communist Party
should respect human rights and the personal dignity of the
disabled even more, because the Party's goal is to liberate
humanity and in a socialist country everybody should be prosperous
and happy.
</P>
<P>
Deng Pufang, chairman of the China Disabled Persons'
Federation, delivered a report on a nationwide campaign to help
the disabled.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the country held the first meeting to
commend outstanding disabled people six years ago, a lot of model
workers have appeared in various walks of lifes.
</P>
<P>
He said that Jiang Zemin's preface elaborates the significance
of the work to help the disabled in an all-round and profound way
with a Maxist perspective. It has also laid a theoretical
foundation for the improvement of this work with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting 120 outstanding disabled persons, 85 units
and 81 persons engaged in helping the disabled, 79 "disabled
families" and 32 workers in the field were cited.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guan'gen and several other senior Chinese officials also
attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yunshan, deputy head of the Propaganda Department of the
CPC Central Committee, asked the public to continue to help the
disabled and learn from the disabled people's spirit of
self-reliance, and set a correct world view and life value
system.
</P>
<P>
Some outstanding disabled persons reported on their experiences in
overcoming difficulties.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Peng Peiyun extended greetings to 60 million
disabled people and their families. She urged governments at
all levels to follow Jiang Zemin's call to further lend a hand
to the disabled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
