<HEADLINE> Australian Insurer Cooperates with PICC Shanghai Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- An Australian insurer today signed
a cooperation agreement with the Shanghai branch of the People's
Insurance Corporation of China Life Insurance Co. Ltd (PICC Life),
the biggest life insurer in Shanghai, China's financial center.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the Australia-based Colonial Mutual
Group will provide assistance to the Chinese side in professional
training and management.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is expected to lay a foundation for further
cooperation in future, such as the establishment of a
joint-venture insurance company in China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese laws now allow foreign financial firms to apply to
operate branches three years after opening representative
offices in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Colonial Mutual Group, a transnational insurance company
with more than 140 branches across Asia, established two offices
in Beijing and Shanghai in 1994.  
