<HEADLINE> Microsoft Building Bond With Chinese PC Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Microsoft Corporation of the
United States will have its products licensed to more Chinese
personal computer manufacturers, distributors, and system
builders, who package the products to be sold with personal
computers, to enhance its sales in China.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft has already signed such licensing agreements with
China's leading personal computer manufacturers, Legend Group,
Tontru Group, and the Great Wall. It has also signed channel
distribution agreements with four delivery service
partners: Electronic Resources (China) Co., Ltd., Laser Computers,
SIS International, and Stargate Technology.
</P>
<P>
Joachim Kempin, senior vice-president of Microsoft, said in a
recent speech in Beijing that the strategy can also benefit the
Chinese personal computer industry, in that Microsoft products
raise not only the publicity but also the overall standard of
Chinese personal computers.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that foreign personal computers accounted for 40
percent of the Chinese market last year and that the rate will
decline this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Qi, an official of the Ministry of Electronics Industry,
told Microsoft officials on Monday that strengthening cooperation
with China's personal computers industry guarantees the long-term
profitability of Microsoft and other western producers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
