<HEADLINE> New Custom Office Opens in Picturesque Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A new custom office opened today in a
mountainous region in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Its establishment in the Wuyi Mountains, a picturesque scenic
area, gives the local economy a bridge to the international market.
</P>
<P>
Local sources reported that there are 187 overseas-funded joint
ventures in the region, most of which are involved in making or
trading in bamboo or wooden products, tea and feed.
</P>
<P>
The new custom office will help overseas investors with the
import and export of commodities, boost the local tourism industry
and promote scientific and cultural exchanges between the province
and foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony was held today for the opening of the custom office,
attended by more than 1,000 local and overseas people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 26 contracts worth a total of 61.4 million US
dollars were signed between the region and overseas investors at a
trade fair held later in the day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
