<HEADLINE> Top US Pharmaceuticals Firm Sets Up Joint Venture in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Schering Pharmaceuticals
Co. Ltd, of the US, ranking 15th among the world's top medicine
manufacturers, set up a joint venture here today.
</P>
<P>
Schering, together with two Chinese drug companies, invested a
total of 37 million US dollars in the venture, the Shanghai
Schering Pharmaceutical Company, which will produce
Schering-brand pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
The company, established in 1851, has set up companies in more
than 40 countries, and has an annual turnover of 4.5 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
