<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Meets Hong Kong Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee, said here today: "All work we do should be
viewed from the angle of Hong Kong's smooth transition and
long-term stability and prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Li, also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the
remark at a meeting with a delegation from the Hong Kong-based
Guangdong Societies' Committee to greet Hong Kong's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is led by Henry Fok Ying-tung, chairman of the
committee and vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li said Hong Kong's return to the motherland is a major
historical event, occupying an important place in the hearts of
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
It is well known to all that, starting from the launching of
the Opium War in 1840 by Britain, which forced the government of
the Qing Dynasty to sign the Treaty of Nanjing and allow the
British to occupy Hong Kong, China was gradually turned into a
semi-feudal and semi-colonial society.
</P>
<P>
From that time on, Li said, countless noble-minded patriots
waged heroic anti-imperialist struggles for national
liberation. Hong Kong's return to the motherland is a historic
event, which indicates the wiping out of shame for the Chinese
nation and indicates the country's growing strength.
</P>
<P>
All sons and daughters of the Chinese nation are encouraged by
this event, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are only 49 days left before Hong Kong
returns to the motherland. The key to maintaining Hong Kong's
smooth transfer of power and its long-term stability and
prosperity is the ability of Hong Kong compatriots to unite,
organize together and earnestly carry out the Basic Law and
consciously proceed from Hong Kong's stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the belief that the Hong Kong compatriots who have
mastered their destiny are certain to govern Hong Kong well and
create new miracles on their own land.
</P>
<P>
He said all the visitors present have done much for the
mainland's reform and opening to the outside world. They have
invested in running schools, offering assistance to those who met
with difficulties, erecting bridges and repairing highways and
importing advanced technology to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
As a result, they have won trust from the people, enjoying high
reputations both in Hong Kong and the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Li said it is his hope that they will value their achievements
which were made not easily and will, as always, make contributions
to the country's construction and their hometowns' prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Fok said that for many years the Hong Kong-based Guangdong
societies have tried their best to provide assistance to their
hometowns and the country as a whole whenever they had
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
As Chinese people, he said, they have the responsibility to
build the country well. The Hong Kong-based Guangdong Societies'
Committee, which is a newly established organization, also has the
obligation to hold celebrations well for Hong Kong's return and
help the government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
safeguard its stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee and
head of the United Front Work Department of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee, attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
