<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Meets Icelandic Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met here this morning with Helgi Agustsson,
permanent undersecretary of Iceland's Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on further development of China-Iceland
friendly cooperative ties and international issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Agustsson, Qian said that bilateral
relations between China and Iceland have witnessed rapid
development in recent years, and there are frequent exchanges of
visits of senior leaders between the two sides, and close
cooperation in economic and trade, scientific and technological
and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
China always holds that all countries, big or small, rich or
poor, are equal members of the international community, Qian said,
adding that China attaches great importance to developing friendly
and cooperative relations with Iceland, and is willing to enhance
such relations.
</P>
<P>
Agustsson said that China has been playing an important role in
international affairs, and will exert an increasingly greater
impact on the establishment of a new world political and economic
order. It is of great importance to maintain exchanges of visits
of senior leaders between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yingfan, China's vice foreign minister, and Hjalmar
W. Hannesson, ambassador of Iceland to China, were present at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Agustsson arrived yesterday as a guest of the Chinese Foreign
Ministry. 
