<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Bonded Zone Celebrates 5th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A group of investment projects
that went into operation today were a special gift for the fifth
birthday of the Guangzhou Bonded Zone, neighboring Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Seven projects becoming operational, as well as five other
projects for which contracts were signed, brought some 48 million
US dollars in total investment, according to Liu Wenzhe, director
of the Administration Committee of the bonded zone.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of March the number of signed projects had
reached 1,319, with 818 million US dollars in total investment,
since the bonded zone was set up five years ago, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
They included 213 overseas investment projects worth 219
million US dollars, Liu noted.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's Huangpu Customs announced today six new measures in
a bid to back the economic development of the area. The measures
focused on simplifying customs procedures, further improving
work efficiency, cracking down upon smuggling, improving
co-operation with other departments concerned, and so on.
</P>
<P>
The bonded area has injected 160 million yuan (about 19 million
US dollars) into the construction of infrastructure in the past
five years, including commodity trading and exhibition areas,
bonded warehouses, a customs building and a container terminal,
Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The volume of imports and exports hit 470 million US
dollars-worth in the area up to the end of the first quarter of
this year. It has also accepted orders for export goods worth more
than 200 million US dollars, Liu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
