<HEADLINE> UNICEF Condemns Attack on Staff by Zairean Armed Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF) today condemned Monday's attack on its staff by five
armed men in military uniforms in the eastern Zairean town of Goma.
</P>
<P>
Carol Bellamy, the agency's executive director described the
attack as "barbaric behavior" and called on leaders of the
Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire to
find and capture those responsible.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF said the armed men, dressed in uniforms of the ADFL led
by Laurent Kabila, threatened and beat two foreign and three
local agency staff in their house. The armed men initially said
they were searching for weapons, but later demanded money.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever the circumstances were, it is absolutely unacceptable
for UNICEF staff should be subjected to such acts of terror,"
Bellamy said in a statement. "It is a total affront to the
fundamental principles of humanitarian assistance," she said.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the ADFL had been informed of the attack. But
ADFL authorities in Goma said it was possible the assailants were
trying to discredit the ADFL by wearing ADFL-style uniforms.
</P>
</TEXT>
