<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets US Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren
met here today with a delegation of the U.S.-China Chamber of
Commerce led by its chairman Prescott Bush.
</P>
<P>
Rong said that he was glad to meet Bush, an old friend of his,
and that he appreciated the meaningful work the chamber has done
for promoting the Sino-U.S. economic and trade ties since its
establishment in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Rong noted that since the two countries set up diplomatic ties,
the bilateral economic and trade relations of cooperation have
achieved fast development and this cannot be separated from the
joint efforts of the two countries' entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Rong expressed belief that following the normal progress of the
bilateral ties, the bilateral economic and trade cooperation will
score even greater advancement.
</P>
<P>
Rong hoped the U.S. chamber will achieve more results in its
cooperation and exchanges with its Chinese counterparts in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Prescott Bush, describing his current China tour as very
successful, said his delegation had fruitful business talks with
their Chinese counterparts in the cities of Beijing, Suzhou,
Tianjin, and Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, mainly composed of managers of small and
medium-sized businesses in the U.S., hoped to cooperate with
similar companies in China, Bush said.
</P>
<P>
Rong said China also attaches great importance to cooperation
with foreign small and medium-sized firms.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. visitors are here as guests of the China Council for
the Promotion of International Trade. 
</P>
