<HEADLINE> Inspection Group to Enforce Product Quality Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature will
inspect the enforcement of Law on Product Quality by sending
inspection groups next month to four of the provinces in east and
central China.
</P>
<P>
The move is intended to continue the efforts to tighten
supervision over and management of quality of products to
safeguard the rights and interests of users and consumers and to
improve the country's economic order.
</P>
<P>
"We must attach greater importance to the issue of product
quality," Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress (NPC), told a meeting here today
for the deployment of law enforcement inspection of product
quality by the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The law enforcement of product quality has a great bearing on
China's economic development and improvement of the people's living
standards, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Law on Product Quality was adopted by the NPC Standing
Committee in February 1993, and relevant laws have been put into
force since then.
</P>
<P>
These laws have played an important role in maintaining the
order of China's socialist market economy and protecting the
rights and interests of users and consumers in the past four
years or so, the vice-chairman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970513.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inspection Group Sent for Enforcement of Product Quality Law (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Governments at various levels and departments in charge of
technical supervision have redoubled their efforts to ensure law
enforcement of product quality since the law entered into force,
Wang said.
</P>
<P>
He added that a strong sense of quality of products has been
built up among residents of the whole nation, product quality has
been steadily improved, and large numbers of enterprises have
begun to pay closer attention to their product quality, marketing
and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
According to the meeting, based on the Law on Product Quality,
the inspection will focus on enforcement of the law by local
governmental institutions and technical supervision departments at
various levels.
</P>
<P>
Four inspection groups will be sent in early June to Guangdong,
Zhejiang, Hebei and Henan provinces, respectively, for 10-day
tours. Meanwhile, the NPC Standing Committee has urged 10 other
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities to make
inspections themselves of the local enforcement of the law. The
areas include Tianjin, Inner Mongolia, Liaoning, Heilongjiang and
Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the State Bureau of Technical Supervision, the
Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuratorate and the
China National Consumers' Association delivered reports on law
enforcement of product quality at the meeting, which was presided
over by Li Hao, member of the NPC Standing Committee and
vice-chairman of the NPC Finance and Economics Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
