<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches Operation Against Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops today
launched a massive operation against the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the country's Northern Province, a military
spokesman announced here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops began an offensive
operation this morning from the Vavuniya area to wrest control of
regions occupied by the LTTE in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The troops have advanced approximately five kilometers into the
LTTE territory and met with little resistance, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that four LTTE rebels were reportedly killed and a
number of others injured, but there were no casualties on the part
of the government troops.
</P>
<P>
The operation had been expected during the last couple of
weeks, according to informed sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that the LTTE rebels had been preparing for
the military onslaught by training their cadres.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the northeast of the
country. 
</P>
