<HEADLINE> China Wins Two Weightlifting Golds with One World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese lifters collected two gold medals
out of four on offer in the weightlifting tournament at the second
East Asian Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Zou Feie, veteran in the Chinese team, also set a world record
in the snatch of the women's 59-kg category while winning the title
for the division.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese girl, who gold medal winner in the 1994 World
Championships, snatched 100 kilograms to beat the previous world mark
by one kilogram. The lifted world record of 99 kilograms was set by
her compatriot Chen Xiaomin at the Asian Championships in 1995.
</P>
<P>
After taking the snatch with an overwhelming weight, Zou Feie
continued her strength to win the jerk at 120 kilograms for a total of
220 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Wu Meiyi of Chinese Taipei had the silver medal at 200 kilograms
while Chung Myong Sook of South Korea won the bronze at 187.5
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Zou Feie, from Hunan Province, had been training in
weightlifting for more than eight years. "I have predicted that I
would set a world record in the snatch, " She said, "If I can lift
to my best."
</P>
<P>
Another gold medal in weightlifting for China was from Zhang Yong,
who beat Ibragim Samadov of Kazakhstan in the men's 83-kg category.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yong, who asked 150kg in the snatch and 190kg in the jerk in
his first attempt only for a place in the final of the eight National
Games in October, posed a strong challenge to Samadov, a veteran in
the Kazakhstanian team.
</P>
<P>
After Zhang Yong snatched 160kg in his second lift in the snatch,
Samadov, who has heavier bodyweight than his Chinese rival, had to ask
165kg in his second try, but he failed twice.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakhstanian failure continued in the clean and jerk, in
which he had 195kgs while Zhang Yong lifted 205kgs, beating Samadov
by 10 kilograms in the total.
</P>
<P>
Yeom Dong Chul of South Korea finished third at 332.5kgs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jui Lien of Chinese Taipei won the women's 64kg division at
217.5kgs and Du Yuxin of China had the silver at 205. The bronze
medal went to South Korean Choi Eon Ja, who collected 190kgs.
</P>
<P>
Lee Kang Seok of South Korea claimed the gold medal in the men's
76kg division with an accumulated lifts of 325 kilograms. Lu Gang of
China, who had the identical weight as Lee Kang Seok, had to be
contended with the second place due to heavier bodyweight.
</P>
<P>
Choi Byung Chan of South Korea was third at 322. 
</P>
</TEXT>
