<HEADLINE> Philippine Coconut Exports Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' coconut exports
went down 30.43 percent to 45.54 million U.S. dollars in March
this year from last year's 66.46 million dollars, official data
showed today.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the National Statistics Office showed that of
coconut products exports, shipments of coconut oil decreased 30.32
percent to 33.04 million dollars from 54.45 million during the
same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Zero transaction registered by copra exports further diminished
export receipts from coconut products, data showed.
</P>
<P>
For the first quarter of 1997, exports of coconut products
reached 179.56 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of desiccated coconut, however, reported an 18.54
percent increase in March this year, hitting 6.5 million dollars
from 5.5 million last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, agro-based coconut products exports amounted to
98.07 million dollars this March, representing a 12.6 percent drop
from 112.15 million in 1996, data showed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
