<HEADLINE> China Takes Two Golds in Swimming at EAG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan each claimed two gold
medals while Kazakhstan had one from five titles on offer in the
swimming competitions at the second East Asian Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
China's Fu Yong set a new games record in the men's 200m backstroke
and won the title with a clocking of two minutes and 0.73 seconds,
beating Japanese swimmer Konnai Keitaro and South Korean Ji Sang Joon
to the second and third. Keitaro was timed 2:02.55 and Ji Sang Joon
was clocked at 2:02.75.
</P>
