an outsanding performance today, and the result is an excellent one."
</P>
<P>
Another gold medal for China was from the women's 4x100m freestyle
relay, in which Chinese quartet beat their Japanese rivals to the
second with a winning time of three minutes 47.39 seconds. Japan was
clocked at 3:52.85 and South Korean finished third at 3:54.26.
</P>
<P>
Japanese swimmers notched up two titles through Miyaji Sachiko and
Nakamura Mai in the women's 400m freestyle and 100m backstroke events
respectively. Sachiko, who was timed four minutes 15.43 second, beat
her compatriot Iwata Reina to the second by 2.18 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Lin Chi Chan of Chinese Taipei finished third in the 400m freestyle
event at 4:17.78.
</P>
<P>
While in the women's 100m backstroke event, Mai sprinted home with
clocking of one minute and 1.76 seconds. Her compatriot Hagiwara
Tomoko was second with 0.58 seconds behind. Chinese swimmer Jia
Yuanyuan was third at 1:02.61.
</P>
<P>
The only other gold medal from the swimming pool went to Serguei
Borissenko of Kazakhstan, who won the men's 100m freestyle at 51.36
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Fukuda Hiroshi of Japan was second at 51.75 and Koh Yun Ho of
South Korea third at 52.17. 
