<HEADLINE> Beijing North Star H Shares Dealings to Commence Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Dealings in the Beijing North
Star Company Limited H shares are expected to commence here
Wednesday, it was announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The company said Monday that a total of 50,426 valid
applications had been received from the local public for a total
of its 36,609,904,000 H shares, equivalent to approximately 397
times the total number of 92,220,000 H shares initially available
for subscription under the New Issue by the public in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The H Share Offer initially involves a New Issue of 92,220,000
H shares and a Placing of 522,580,000 H shares at a price of 2.4
Hong Kong dollars (about 30 U.S. cents) per share to raise a total
of 1.48 billion Hong Kong dollars (about 189.74 million
U.S. dollars), a spokeswoman for the company told reporters here
today.
</P>
<P>
According to her, HSBC Investment Bank Asia Limited is the
global coordinator, sponsor and lead manager of the H Share Offer.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Sha Wanquan, chairman and general manager of the Beijing
North Star, told reporters: "We are most delighted that our
flotation has met with an overwhelming market response. The
subscription result is valid proof of investors' recognition of
Beijing North Star's achievements in the past and confidence in
our future plans and strategies."
</P>
<P>
He also expressed optimism about the Beijing property market in
the future.  
</P>
