<HEADLINE> China to Increase Economic Cooperation with Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China will increase efforts to
promote trade and economic cooperation with countries in Latin
America, according to a forum on the Latin American market that
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 24 Chinese enterprises across the country
are optimistic about cooperation with the region, and departments
plan to set up a Sino-Latin American economic cooperation and
trade development company, to encourage contacts.
</P>
<P>
China has economic and trade relations with all countries in
Latin America, and Sino-Latin American cooperation has maintained
rapid growth in 1990s. Bilateral trade volume exceeded 6.7 billion
US dollars last year, a year-on-year increase of 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Latin America may become another international investment
resort, some Chinese entrepreneurs agreed.
</P>
<P>
The area is rich in iron ore, copper, wool, wheat, and paper
pulp, which China needs in economic development, while China's
light industry products, textiles, electronics, and machinery sell
well in the Latin American market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
