<HEADLINE> IMT Growth Triangle Attracts Huge Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The
Indonesia-Malaysia-Thailand Growth Triangle (IMT-GT) area,
established through memorandums of understanding signed among the
three countries, has attracted huge investments from the private
sector.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad told the Senate today
that 47 projects involving 11 billion ringgit (about 4.4 billion
U.S. dollars) have been planned or implemented by the private
sector in the IMT-GT area.
</P>
<P>
He said the projects cover transportation, telecommunications,
tourism, industry, trade, finance, energy, agriculture and human
resource development.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 14 projects have been implemented while the rest
are in various stages of implementation, he said during the
question time.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader said the main purpose of the IMT-GT is to
enable the private sectors of the three countries to pool their
resources and spearhead economic development through close
cooperation for their common benefit.
</P>
<P>
He said the implementation of the projects would have a big
effect on development in the IMT-GT area.  
</P>
