<HEADLINE> Malaysian King to Visit Hungary, Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar
will pay state visits to Hungary and Poland beginning May 19, it
was announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The king, to be accompanied by Queen Tuanka Najihah, will be in
Hungary for five days from May 19 and in Poland for three days
from May 26, the Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
This will be the king's first state visits to East European
countries since he was enthroned in September 1994.
</P>
<P>
The visits are important for enhancing bilateral relations and
cooperation with the two East European countries, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Minister in the Prime Minister's Department Abdul Hamid Othman
and senior government officials will also accompany the royal
couple on the visits.
</P>
<P>
Their programs include meetings with the two countries'
presidents, prime ministers and parliament speakers.
</P>
<P>
In Budapest, the Hungarian capital, the king will lay a wreath
at the Heroes Square and be presented with the key to Budapest by
the city's mayor.
</P>
<P>
The royal visit to Poland includes a wreath-laying ceremony at
the "Tomb of the Unknown Soldier," a tour of the Old City and a
trip to Krakow, the old capital of Poland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
