<HEADLINE> Shanghai Leases out Land-Use Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Twelve large business groups in
Shanghai have been transferred the right to use the state-owned
land.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal Administration of Real Estate signed
respective agreements with the 12 conglomerates on May 10 and
leased out 32.9 million sq m of land to the conglomerates which
have been authorized to exercise management over housing
properties with a combined floor space of 308,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
The move is intended to change the past practices under which
units use state-owned land assigned to them forever or use rented
state-owned housing properties permanently, and to enliven
state-owned real estate sector, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The conglomerates are authorized to exercise the right to
management and operation over their respective land and housing
properties assigned to them, while making sure that the state-owned
real estate properties will increase in value.
</P>
<P>
They can also re-lease or exchange such properties, so as to
increase their respective total assets and to establish a new
property right that is compatible with the modern enterprise
system, said the officials.
</P>
<P>
In China, all land is state-owned.  
</P>
</TEXT>
