<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Rocks Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake with an estimated
magnitude of 6.1 on the open-ended Richter scale jolted Japan's
main southwestern island of Kyushu this afternoon, the
Meteorological Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which struck around 2:35 p.m.(local
time), was 20 kilometers below the ground in Satsuma, Kagoshima
Prefecture, southern Kyushu, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of injuries.
</P>
<P>
The agency said there was no threat of tsunami, or tidal wave,
from the quake. 
