<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed on
the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index continued to rise, gaining another 11.49 points to close at
2112.97 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume fell to 132.54 million units, valued at
474.97 million Singapore dollars (about 327.57 million U.S.
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 219 to 120 while 282
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Elec was the most actively traded stock as it posted a turnover
of 14.49 million units. The Singapore Telecom had 9.13 million of
its shares traded while Popular Book Store saw 5.67 million of its
shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
City Developments warrant 98 and local beverage and food maker
F&AMP;N shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them rose
by 30 cents to finish at 10.7 and 11.9 Singapore dollars
respectively. Yeo HSS gained 25 cents to end at 5.45 Singapore
dollars while the Singapore Technologies Aero Foreign picked up by
21 cents to close at 2.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, sound card maker Creative 50 was the biggest
loser as it declined by 2.1 Singapore dollars to end at 26.9
dollars. Malaya Banking fell by 80 cents to close at 14.5
Singapore dollars, and GE Life finished 40 cents lower at 20
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
