<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Ceremonies for New Through Train Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kowloon-Canton Railway
Corporation (KCRC) will hold two ceremonies on May 19 and 20 for
the opening of the through train services between Beijing and Hong
Kong and between Shanghai and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Mabel Wan, manager of KCRC's Media and Community Affairs
Section, said here today that the train from Beijing will arrive
at Kowloon at 13:10 on May 19 and will depart from Kowloon for
Beijing at 15:00 the same day.
</P>
<P>
Both journeys will take 29 hours and 55 minutes and the trains
will stop at six intermediate stations, including Changping,
Guangzhou East, Guangzhou, Changsha, Wuchang and Zhengzhou.
</P>
<P>
The train from Shanghai will arrive at Kowloon at 13:00 on May
20 and will leave Kowloon for Shanghai at 15:00.
</P>
<P>
The journeys between Shanghai and Hong Kong will take 29 hours
and 18 minutes and the trains will call at four intermediate
stations, including Changping, Guangzhou East, Guangzhou and
Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Trains for the services are provided by China's Railway
operators and consist of 12 coaches each, consisting of hard beds,
soft beds and deluxe cabins. The maximum capacity of each train
is 448 passengers.
</P>
<P>
There will be one train to either destination on alternate days
and immigration procedures for Hong Kong will be carried out at
Kowloon (Hung Kom) Station and for China at Changping Station.
</P>
<P>
KCRC now operates other two through train services between Hong
Kong and Guangzhou and between Hong Kong and Zhaoqing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
