<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Army Launches New Operation Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Government troops launched a
massive operation today to wrest control of areas occupied by
Tamil rebels in Northern Province of Sri Lanka, according to
informed sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that they have received reports from Red Cross
 officials based in north Vavuniya Town. The officials heard
artillery fire at day break and noticed troop movement.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that Army Commander General Daluwatte was
reported to be present in Vavuniya Town this morning to oversee
the operation.
</P>
<P>
The sources explained that the operation was expected to get
under way any moment during the last couple of weeks. Earlier
reports indicated that the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
was too preparing to face the military onslaught by training their
cadres.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's air force planes and helicopter gunships are
expected to join the advancing troops to provide air cover, said
the sources, adding that no details were available so far.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been carrying out a 14-year guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
</TEXT>
