<HEADLINE> China to Dispatch Plane with Relief Goods to Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China announced today that it
will soon dispatch an aircraft loaded with relief goods of
food, medicine and blankets to quake victims of Iran.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Embassy in Iran told Xinhua that it has informed
the Iranian Red Crescent Society about the aid on behalf of
the Chinese Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
It said that the relief goods are worth 500,000 Yuan (about
60,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Iran said that rescue operation for the quake victims in
eastern Iran has been largely wound up except for four villages
and international assistance are pouring into Iran.
</P>
<P>
France, Switzerland, Pakistan and Kuwait have sent foods and
medicines for quake victims of Iran on board in five flights.
</P>
<P>
The Red Crescent Society of Turkey Monday sent 20 tonnes of
goods, comprising of sugar, medicines, blankets, cooking oil and
rice.
</P>
<P>
A powerful earthquake hid Birjand, about 800 kilometers east of
Tehran, capital of Iran on May 10, killing at least 2,500 people
and wounding thousands more. 
</P>
</TEXT>
