<HEADLINE> French President to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen
Guofang announced at a routine news conference here today that
President Jacques Chirac of France will pay a state visit to China
from May 15 to 18 at the invitation of Chinese President Jiang
Zemin.
</P>
<P>
When asked about the significance of this visit, Shen said that
both China and France, as two permanent members of the Security
Council of the United Nations, assume important responsibilities
in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
With the acceleration of the world's multi-polarization, Shen
said, both China and France hope to increase consultations and
cooperation in various fields and set up a long-term stable
friendly and cooperative relationship for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"This is not only in the fundamental interests of both
countries, but also conducive to world peace and stability", Shen
added.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that during French President Chirac's visit,
Chinese leaders will have a wide-ranging and in-depth exchange of
views with him, and a joint statement concerning their views on
international situation and their aspiration and determination
to further strengthen bilateral ties is expected to be issued.
</P>
<P>
Shen voiced his conviction that the French president's visit
will achieve substantial results in both political and economic
aspects, and it will be of great significance guiding the future
development of Sino-French relations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, this visit by President Chirac will have a profound
impact internationally, the spokesman said. 
</P>
