<HEADLINE> France Returns Stolen Nigerian Aritifacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 13 (Xinhua) -- France on Monday returned three
pieces of recovered stolen artifacts to Nigeria, the Guardian
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The artifacts were handed over to the Nigerian Minister of
Information and Culture Walter Ofonagaro by the French Ambassador
to Nigeria, Philipe Peltier, in Abuja.
</P>
<P>
The recovery was made possible by the International Criminal
Police Commission (INTERPOL) and the French government, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Ofonagaro commended the French government for the gesture and
appealed to the international community, perticularly the British
government to repatriate other artifacts stolen from Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Lamenting that "a great deal of Nigerian art works still flood
Europe and America", the Nigerian minister blamed the situation
on unscrupulous Nigerians and their foreign collaborators and
advocated stiffer penalty for them. 
</P>
