<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Firm Ahead of Federal Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
firmer but trading remained subdued ahead of the release of the
1997-98 federal budget tonight.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 78.21 U.S. cents from 77.83 at
yesterday's close.
</P>
<P>
Westpac Bank's debt securities chief dealer Anthony Robson said
that if the underlying deficit figure comes to around 2 billion
Australian dollars (1.56 billion U.S. dollars) tonight, the market
"would probably see a rally."
</P>
<P>
The market expects that the government will be able to pay off
its debt in the 1997-98 financial year, with no new issues of
Australian bonds in the coming year and the possibility that the
government will actually buy back bonds.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the local unit rose to 93.32 against the
Japanese yen from 92.49 at the close yesterday and it was at 1.331
from 1.3107 against the Deutsche mark.  
</P>
