<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
reached another record high today as banking stocks surged on
expectations of positive results.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 9.5 points up at
2534.3.
</P>
<P>
The previous record close on the all ordinaries was set on May
9 when the market closed at 2526 points.
</P>
<P>
"Today's profit announcement by St. George Bank was at the
higher end of expectations and augured well for tomorrow's interim
results for Westpac Bank and Thursday's National Australia Bank
results", said Jamie Spiteri from Shaw Stockbroking.
</P>
<P>
The leading banking stock today was Commonwealth Bank which
rose 19 cents, while ANZ increased nine cents. Westpac Bank
improved eight cents and National Australia Bank was 15.7 cents
higher.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index was up 10.5 points at 3967.5, while
the resources index was 9.4 points higher at 1431.9.
</P>
<P>
A total of 322.77 million shares were traded today worth 781.92
million Australian dollars (609.8 million U.S. dollars). 
