<HEADLINE>   Cypriot President Rushed to Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides
was rushed to the Nicosia General Hospital in the early hours
today after he felt minor pains in his chest.
</P>
<P>
A medical report from the hospital said "the results of the
medical examinations are considered satisfactory" after the
president underwent catheterization and angiography this morning.
</P>
<P>
The president, who will leave hospital early this afternoon,
is expected to return to his normal duties Wednesday, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
It added that President Clerides, 78, has felt rather unwell
in the past couple of days and Monday evening he was seen by his
doctors who recommended he be admitted to hospital for medical
checkups.
</P>
<P>
The doctors recommended that the president should not travel
to China, where he is scheduled to pay a five-day official
visit starting this weekend. 
