<HEADLINE> Treasury Bonds Well Received in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China's first series of
unregistered treasury bonds this year has met with great investor
enthusiasm in Shanghai, the country's largest economic center.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Shanghai residents bought nearly 2.88
billion yuan (about 346 million US dollars) in unregistered bonds
between May 1-6, about 56.6 percent of the total allocated for
sale in the municipality.
</P>
<P>
The three-year bonds, valued at 40 billion yuan in aggregate,
were put on sale on May 1. They can be traded immediately after
the issue closes on May 31. The bonds carry an annual coupon rate
of 9.18 percent.
</P>
<P>
China's annual treasury bond issue has expanded rapidly in
recent years. The volume last year reached 196 billion yuan. This
year's value is estimated at 248.5 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
