opening process, and congratulated China on its coming resumption
of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Castro added that Cuba would continue to support China's
peaceful unification cause and efforts to enter into the World
Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Li attended a reception hosted by Castro in the evening. Cuba
is the second stop of Li's six-nation Latin American trip. The
Chinese vice-premier will also visit Colombia, Chile and
Argentina. 
