<HEADLINE> Britain Retains Sanctions Against Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The new British Labor government
will retain the limited economic sanctions imposed on Nigeria in
1993 by the Conservative government, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the new government's foreign policy in London on
Monday, Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said human rights would be
the center piece of the new government's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
He alleged that economic sanctions are necessary to ensure
that democratic rights are restored to Nigerians.
</P>
<P>
Britain joined the United States and the European Union in
imposing sanctions on Nigeria at the annulment of the June 12,
1993 elections.
</P>
<P>
The sanctions include ban on visa to top government officials
and their families, freezing of development aid package, sports
boycott and halting of any financial assistance to government.
</P>
