</P>
<P>
The operation to unearth the victims is continuing in the four
villages.
</P>
<P>
The state television reported 4,000 deaths Monday night.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rainfall has soaked many parts
of South Korea over the past two days, causing traffic accidents
and many casualties.
</P>
<P>
So far, the highest falls in the southwestern and the
southeastern parts of the country stand at 115.8 mm and 142.5 mm,
the Yonhap News Agence reported.
</P>
