<HEADLINE> Living Conditions to be Monitored in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May (Xinhua) -- Zambia's Central Statistics Office
(CSO) will from this year embark on an annual exercise of
monitoring the living conditions of Zambians throughout the
country, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The move is expected to be carried out through a living
conditions monitoring unit that was newly established in the CSO.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Minister of Information and Broadcasting Services
David Mpamba recently said that the survey of living conditions
is a necessary tool of measuring the level of development in the
country other than just using economic indicators.
</P>
<P>
Mpamba said that development of economic growth could not be
measured only by the Gross Domestic Product (GDP), inflation
rates or other economic measures which did not provide a
comprehensive picture of real development.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "development is only when such economic growth is
accompanied by improvement in the living conditions of the people
that we can confidently say there has been national development."
</P>
