<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Establish Tourism Revolving Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government plans to
establish a tourism revolving fund to provide loans to indigenous
entrepreneurs seeking to participate in the lucrative industry
currently dominated by whites or foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Opening the Matetsi Game Lodge, 33 km west of Victoria Falls
of north Zimbabwe yesterday, President Robert Mugabe, who was
concerned by the low level participation by indigenous
entrepreneurs in the industry, said the fund was meant to make
their entry into the industry easier.
</P>
<P>
"The revolving fund will have some shares in the new project
while indigenous operators retain the option to buy out the
fund," he said.
</P>
<P>
The government wants participation of blacks in the
fast-growing tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said he was concerned about the social, economic and
environmental problems highlighted in an environment impact
assessment study undertaken by the World Conservation Union.
</P>
<P>
He urged local operators in the tourism industry to be
disciplined in their use of natural resources. 
</P>
