<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Leader Meets Vietnamese Party School Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee, met with a delegation from the Ho Chi Minh
National Political Academy (HCMNPA) of Vietnam here today.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee and president of the Party School of the CPC Central
Committee, said that friendly contacts between the CPC and the
Communist Party of Vietnam have been increasing with the
continuous growth of party-to-party relations and bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Communications between the CPC party school and the HCMNPA will
help deepen mutual understanding and exchange experience in
training cadres.
</P>
<P>
Head of the delegation To Huy Rua, who is a member of the
Central Committee of the Vietnamese Communist Party and also
standing vice-director of HCMNPA, said that China's great
achievements in the reform and opening up drive have deeply
impressed the delegation.
</P>
<P>
The delegation has gained a great deal of enlightenment from
the CPC's experience in party building and party school
management, he said, adding the HCMNPA is willing to expand
contacts with the Party School of the CPC Central
Committee. 
</P>
