<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Speed up Exploration of Mineral Resources in Southwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The "China Economic Herald"
reported that the State Planning Commission and the Ministry of
Geology and Mineral Resources have jointly drafted a plan to
intensify prospecting of mineral resources in mountainous areas
among Jinsha, Lanchang, and Nujiang rivers in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The two ministerial organizations said in the opinion document
that they will work hard and spend five to eight years to produce
a comprehensive report about mineral resource distribution in the
mountainous areas, and will carry out mining on a fairly-large
scale, in areas where conditions permit, to advance regional
economic development.
</P>
<P>
They will also outline the geological prospecting work plan for
the Ninth Five-Year-Plan Period (1996-2000), which has been under
intense drafting at the moment, and will also list the region as
one of the key geological prospecting areas and will work out
preferential policies to advance prospecting in the forthcoming
years.
</P>
<P>
The two organizations will also cooperate closely with the
State Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
General survey of mineral resources in major areas will be
intensified and investment in similar surveys and prospecting will
be encouraged, said the opinion document.
</P>
<P>
Pre-stage planning and negotiations to explore mineral
resources in the region should also be organized in an active
way. Paid use of the rights for prospecting and mining will also
be encouraged.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to reform the management system of
geological prospecting and the mining business.
</P>
<P>
The opinion document also called on governments at various
levels to increase investment in the prospecting of mineral
resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
