<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Vinyon N Facility Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 13 -- China's first 5,000-tonnage Vinyon N
production facility was put in operation in Fushun, a
petrochemical city in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Vinyon N is a flame-retarded acrylic fiber that can be widely
used to produce flame-retarded fabrics, toys, and fire-proof
clothes. Only a few countries are capable of producing the fiber
for its production procedures are complex. China used to rely
solely on import to obtain the product.
</P>
<P>
China purchased the main equipment of the project from Italy,
German, Japan, and Switzerland at the cost of 550 million yuan
while using home-made supporting equipment.
</P>
<P>
After a half month of trial operation, the facility has been
proved to operate well and meet the design standards. Its products
have already been exported to a dozen of countries, including
the European Community and the United States. The facility
is expected to earn 3.5 million US dollars in hard currency a
year after full operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
