<HEADLINE> Farm Machinery Popular in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Farm machines are helping Chinese
farmers reap good harvests in Sanya, south China's island province
of Hainan as its early rice harvest season comes due.
</P>
<P>
In the paddy fields of Tongjing Village, combines are doing a
much quicker and better job, finishing the harvesting work in less
than half a day that required two or three days if done by
hands. Combine drivers have become favorite guests in the
villages. Machine reapers also yield ten percent more grain.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in the city are competing to buy farm machinery. And
some less wealthy families plan to put their money together to buy
a reaper next year.
</P>
<P>
More than 26,000, or more than half of the households have
bought agricultural machines. Of the city's more than 50
million yuan of machinery sales to date, farmers contributed over
30 million yuan, according to the local farm machinery department.
</P>
</TEXT>
