<HEADLINE> South Korea Soaked by Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rainfall has soaked many parts
of South Korea over the past two days, causing traffic accidents
and many casualties.
</P>
<P>
So far, the highest falls in the southwestern and the
southeastern parts of the country stand at 115.8 mm and 142.5 mm,
the Yonhap News Agence reported.
</P>
<P>
The rain has forced many domestic airlines to suspend flights,
and 90,000 fishing boats were called back. In the middle area of
the country, more than 60 traffic accidents happened, killing
eight and injuring about 80.
</P>
<P>
The rain came in the middle of the second East Asian Games in
Busan City, and in an international flower show in Goyang, and
inconvenienced both.
</P>
<P>
The Meteorological Bureau in South Korea gave a warning, but
said the rain had helped alleviate the draught that began last
winter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
