<HEADLINE> India's Software Exports to Increase Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- India's booming computer software
industry is likely to reach an export target of 3.6 billion U.S.
dollars by the year 2000, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
According to industry sources here, the figure can be doubled
if Indian exporters undertake a fraction of projects which
companies worldwide are offering to tackle the "year 2000 problem"
when all computer dates will register 00 unless billions of
software lines are rewritten.
</P>
<P>
