<HEADLINE> Italy to Send Aid to Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Italy is sending aid worth about
325,700 U.S. dollars to Iran after a powerful earthquake hit the
eastern part of the country and killed thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
Italy will ferry 36 tons of medicines and other supplies by air
from Pisa, valued at 500 million Lires (295,700 dollars), Italian
Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said in a condolences message to
his Iranian counterpart, Ali Akbar Velayati.
</P>
<P>
Italy will also donate about 30,000 dollars to the United
Nations (U.N.) to purchase medical supplies for Iran in response
to Iran's appeal to the U.N. for assistance, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
"In the face of the terrible tragedy I extend sincere
condolences on behalf of the Italian government and in my own
name," Dini said.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, measuring 7.1 on the Richter scale, jolted the
rural area in eastern Iran on Saturday, killing about 2,400 people
and injuring 40,000. It was the most disastrous earthquake in the
country since 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
