<HEADLINE> Multi-National Exercise Launched in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A multi-national military exercise
called "Savior '97" was launched today on the territory of the
Republic of Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The five-day manoeuvre was jointly organized by Macedonia and
the United States, and within the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization's (NATO) plan of partnership for peace.
</P>
<P>
The major aim of the exercise was to simulate a rescue
operation after a strong earthquake in central Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Besides Macedonia and the U.S., other NATO members and partners
including Italy, Greece, Turkey, Bulgaria, Romania, Albania and
the Republic of Slovenia, took part.
</P>
<P>
Hungary, Poland and the Czech Republic sent teams to watch the
manoeuvre.
</P>
<P>
A strong earthquake, nine on the Richter scale, hit the Macedonian
capital, Skoplje, on July 26, 1963, destroying 80 percent of
the city and leaving more than 1,000 people dead. 
