<HEADLINE> Poland to Get More Loan For Highway Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Poland will get one billion
U.S. dollars from the European Investment Bank (EIB) in the next
three years to build up highways.
</P>
<P>
Polish Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Marek Belka
made the announcement after meeting with EIB Vice Governor
Wolfgang Roth here on Monday, the Polish Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Poland received 1.4 billion ECU (about 1.61 billion dollars)
from the EIB between 1990-1996 to build part of a highway linking
Berlin and Kiev, expand the Warsaw airport and renovate the
Warsaw-Berlin Railway.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the EIB provided a total of five billion ECU
(about six billion dollars) to the Central and East European
countries.
</P>
<P>
Poland plans to build 2,600 kilometers of highways within 15 to
18 years to meet the demands of domestic and foreign
transportation. 
