<HEADLINE> Albania Opposes Enlarged Multinational Force Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha said
today that authority of the multinational force in Albania should
not be expanded.
</P>
<P>
Berisha expressed this at his first press conference since the
country was plunged into chaos in February over the collapse of a
pyramid investment scheme which left thousands of families
penniless.
</P>
<P>
Only by maintaining neutrality could the multinational force
complete its mission in Albania, the president noted.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council passed a resolution on
March 25 authorizing the dispatch of a 6,000-member, Italian-led
multinational force for three months to protect relief operations
and help restore order to Albania.
</P>
<P>
Expanding the multinational forces' authority could lead to an
unprecedentedly complicated situation, Berisha said.
</P>
<P>
On the parliamentary election scheduled for the end of June,
the president said that the election is vital for Albania and
called on all political parties to guarantee its peacefulness and
fairness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
