<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister I.K. Gujral and his Pakistan counterpart
Nawaz Sharif Monday agreed to set up working groups to discuss all
outstanding issues between the two countries including the Kashmir
dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India
</P>
<P>
-- The Delhi High Court Monday stayed the proceedings in the
bribery case of MPs pending before a trial court. Former prime
minister P.V. Narasimha Rao was involved in it.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman
</P>
<P>
-- Sitaram Kesri is trying his best to ensure his election to
the post of Congress president through a consensus, even as
infighting in the party units in some states continues to be a
cause of concern.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Life Insurance Corporation's mandatory investments in
government securities will soon be lowered.  
</P>
