<HEADLINE> 10th SAARC Summit to Be Held in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The tenth summit of the
seven-member countries of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) will be held in Sri Lanka in 1998, according
to informed sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that earlier Sri Lanka sought to jump the
queue and host the 9th summit to coincide with the 50th
anniversary of the country's independence.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaratunga has taken up the
request with leaders of the SAARC who are now holding their ninth
summit in the Maldives, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Under normal circumstances, the 10th summit should be hosted by
Nepal and one after that by Pakistan and Sri Lanka's turn would
not come until the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
They added that it is learnt that Nepal and Pakistan have
agreed to the request made by President Kumaratunga.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, formed in December 1985 to promote regional
cooperation, embraces Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Pakistan, Nepal and Sri Lanka.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
