<HEADLINE> Argentina Coins Mark UNICEF Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Argentine's Central Bank will
put into circulation two coins Tuesday to commemorate the 50th
anniversary of the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF).
</P>
<P>
The coins, with face values of one peso (about one U.S. dollar)
and 50 cents respectively, will total two million, a bulletin of
the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The one-peso coin bears the image of a girl playing with a rag
doll and carries the words "In union and liberty." The reverse
side reads "UNICEF, 50 years for the children."
</P>
<P>
On both sides there are faces of children of different races
and nationalities.
</P>
<P>
The coin was designed by Pedro Rodriguez Dufour, an artist who
works for the Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
The representative for UNICEF in Argentina, Patricio Fuentes,
thanked the Argentine government for the initiative. He said this
was the first time in the world that the UNICEF has been paid
tribute to the minting of a coin of legal tender. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
