<HEADLINE> Yunnan Cane Sugar Output Tops One Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
produced a record 1.06 million tons of cane sugar during the last
pressing season from December 1996 to April 1997, 230,000 tons
more than that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the provincial agricultural
department, cane sugar production generated 1.8 billion yuan in
output value in the last pressing season, bringing in an average
of 450 yuan for four million local sugar cane-growing peasants
each.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the steady production increase to
favorable geographical conditions and enhanced effort which helped
expand its sugar cane-growing areas to 160,000 ha, increasing the
province's sugarcane production from 4.78 million tons to 10
million tons in seven years.
</P>
<P>
Daily production capacity of 83 local sugar refineries
climbed in seven years from 58,000 tons to the current 103,500
tons.
</P>
<P>
By now, the province has 14 percent of the country's cane
sugar market shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
