<HEADLINE> Indonesia Mourns Iran's Loss in Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia has conveyed its
sympathies to Iran on the great loss of lives and material damage
the latter suffered in last Saturday's devastating earthquake in
eastern Iran.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's sympathies were contained in a message sent by
President Soeharto Monday to his Iranian counterpart Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani, the Foreign Ministry said today in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Similar condolences were also expressed by Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas in a separate letter to his Iranian counterpart Ali Akbar
Velayati, said the release.
</P>
<P>
The disastrous earthquake, measuring 7.1 on the Richter scale,
destroyed at least 200 villages, caused extensive damage in
several towns and killed some 2,400 people, reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
