<HEADLINE> Ramos to Keynote World Tourism Meeting in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
would make a keynote address at the 5th session of the World
Tourism Leaders Meeting to be held here on May 20-22.
</P>
<P>
The event, according to Tourism Secretary Mina Gabor, would be
hosted by the Philippines and the World Tourism Organization,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to draw some 300 delegates from 60
nations and regions, including tourism ministers, professionals
from the academia and chief executive officers from the private
sector.
</P>
<P>
Gabor said social and cultural issues affecting tourism
worldwide would be the main topic of the event.
</P>
<P>
participants would study the positive socio-cultural
ramifications of tourism such as increased employment
opportunities, higher income and improved conditions of the
population, she added.
</P>
<P>
They would also tackle issues like the rising incidence of
crime, drug use, prostitution and pedophilia connected with
tourism, Gabor said.
</P>
<P>
The participants would elect a new secretary-general for the
World Tourism Organization during the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
