<HEADLINE> Inter-American Tax Meeting Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The 31st general meeting of
the Inter-American Center of Tax Administrators was opened here
today to find ways to ensure efficient taxation.
</P>
<P>
About 280 experts from across America will analyze the
contribution of funds from tax administration, ways of improving
management of human resources, and upgrading information systems and
legal faculties to collect tax arrears.
</P>
<P>
Opening the meeting, Argentine President Carlos Menem said that
tax evasion "is one of the worst crimes," and the fulfillment of
tax obligations, "a form of exercising one's right to vote."
</P>
<P>
While emphasizing the importance of a sound and efficient tax
management, which he said enables the state to provide essential
services, he thanked Argentine tax workers for collecting record
taxes in the past few months.
</P>
<P>
Menem urged the experts to put forth new proposals to help fair
and just taxation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
