<DOCNO> XIE19970513.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Belarus Sign Border Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma and
his visiting Belarusian counterpart, Alexander Lukashenko, signed
a treaty today on border divisions, along with other 10 agreements.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma told the press after the signing ceremony that the two
countries, which shared a border of 1,200 kilometers, had been
cooperative while negotiating the border issues.
</P>
<P>
Both countries believed that the agreements, the first such
accords ever signed between the countries of the Commonwealth of
Independent States, would pave the way for broader cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The other agreements concerned promoting border trade, and
diminishing the consequences of the Chernobyl nuclear disaster,
both in Ukraine and Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said that both sides should get rid of trade
barriers in order to boost bilateral trade. Trade volume between
Ukraine and Belarus exceeded one billion U.S. dollars in 1996,
with a trade surplus on the Ukrainian side of 400 million dollars.
</P>
