<HEADLINE> Macedonia to Promote Relations With Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov
said Monday in Skoplje that the time is ripe for Macedonia and
Greece to promote relations, according to a report from Skoplje.
</P>
<P>
"It is time for Macedonia and Greece to establish genuine and
sincere relations," as they share "the same strategic goals," said
Gligorov while meeting a Greek press delegation.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the disputes between the two countries over the
name of Macedonia, Gligorov said the Republic of Macedonia is
quite different from the geographic conception of historic
Macedonia, with the former being a concrete country having its own
borders, culture and constitution. It is not reasonable to change
the name, the president said.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia and Greece have held differences over Macedonia's
right to use the name since 1991 when Macedonia declared
independence from the former Yugoslav federation. The United
Nations recognized it under the provisional name of the Former
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia pending a settlement.
</P>
<P>
Greece views that it is not right to name the country
"Macedonia", because it implies its territorial designs on the
northern Greek province of the same name. 
</P>
</TEXT>
