<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Seizes 16 Tons of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan seized 16 tons of
illegal drugs in the first four months of this year, Deputy Prime
Minister Imangali Tasmagambetov said today.
</P>
<P>
In a briefing to a special European Union delegation,
Tasmagambetov, who is also the Chairman of the Kazakhstan Drug
Control Committee, said there has been a 20 percent increase in
drug-related crimes in the country over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan's location and its relatively free borders have made
it an ideal transitional place for international drug rings, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a 130,000 hectare valley in southern Kazakhstan
produces around 5000 tons of marijuana each year, he said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Kazakhstan Government has established many
working groups to combat drug problems, and in March it worked out
a two-year anti-drug program. 
</P>
