<HEADLINE> Tornado Blows Through Downtown Miami on U.S. East Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A tornado whirled past high-rise
condominiums in the U.S. coastal city of Miami today, smashing
windows and sending terrified residents scrambling for cover.
</P>
<P>
Some minor injuries were reported in the city of Florida state
on the east coast of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The storm touched down on the MacArthur Causeway to the south
of Miami shortly before 2:00 p.m. local time (18:00 GMT) and
brought busy midday traffic to a halt, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
As it uprooted trees, hurled branches and other debris and
shattered the glass facades of several structures, the biggest
problem was expected to be accidents caused by lost traffic signs.
</P>
<P>
Several local television stations captured the footage of the
funnel cloud as it blew through the downtown area.
</P>
<P>
An American Airlines jet flying into Miami International
Airport hit severe turbulence because of the tornado, but the
plane managed to land safely. 
</P>
