<HEADLINE> Embryo Transplant Technique Successful in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zhejiang Provincial Academy of
Agricultural Sciences has successfully bred two calves, one male
and the other female, by using an embryo transplantation technique.
</P>
<P>
The accuracy rate of the sex identification is 100 percent, the
first of its kind in the province, a spokesman for the academy
said.
</P>
<P>
The technique involves defrosting a frozen embryo and
cultivating it in-vitro before transplanting into the womb of a
cow or sheep.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Zhejiang Provincial Academy of Agricultural
Sciences defrosted the embryos of seven quality cattle and then
transplanted them into seven cows. As a result, four cows were
fertilized and two made deliveries this March.
</P>
<P>
The technique will accelerate the breeding of quality domestic
animals, according to Yu Songdong, an assistant researcher of the
academy, explaining that ordinary domestic animals will be able to
be used to breed quality ones in larger numbers, and the breeding
cycle of the quality species will be greatly shortened, too.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
