<HEADLINE> Larsson Edges Ferreira at Italian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Sweden Magnus Larsson edged South
Africa's Wayne Ferreira, a semifinalist for the past two years, in
the first round of the Italian Open on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The defeat made Ferreira, the ninth seed here, angrily threw
his racket at a chair after losing the match of 4-6, 7-5, 7-6.
</P>
<P>
Monday's matches also saw some seeds' defeat. Mark
Philippoussis of Australia lost in straight sets to Morocco's
Karim Alami, ranked 68 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis, the big-serving number 16 seed, was defeated
6-2, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Ferreira wasted four matchpoints at 5-3 on Larsson's serve in
the second set and one more when serving for the match at 5-4
before allowing his opponent to level at one set apiece.
</P>
<P>
For Larsson, number 41 in the world after fighting back from
injury, it was his third big victory on clay this season.
</P>
<P>
Last month he fought back from a set down to defeat French Open
champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov in Barcelona and world number one Pete
Sampras in Monte Carlo.
</P>
<P>
There were no problems for defending champion Thomas Muster and
last year's runner-up Richard Krajicek.
</P>
<P>
Number three seed Muster of Austria beat wild card Marzio
Martelli 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Wimbledon champion Krajicek was made to fight in the first set
by Diego Nargiso before firing down a series of unstoppable first
serves to win 7-5, 6-3.  
</P>
</TEXT>
