<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan to Make Tourism Pillar Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan has just
passed a resolution to make tourism a pillar industry for this
land-locked province.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, the province has witnessed a
booming tourism industry as currently the sector has over 140
hotels open to foreign travelers, over 170 travel agencies, over
1,000 tourism buses and vessels, and a total staff of over 50,000.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the province earned 9.7 billion yuan from the local
tourism sector, which accounted for 3.3 percent of the year's
gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
To make tourism its pillar industry, the province will divert
more investment to the industry and more preferential policies
will be adopted for the purpose, said Song Bairui, governor of
Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
Investors from all sectors are encouraged to pour their money
into the business, and meanwhile foreign funds are also welcome,
he said.
</P>
<P>
To improve the environment for the local tourism industry,
greater efforts will be made to build infrastructure, including
building more roads and starting more luxury tourist buses and
passenger-trains.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more flights will be open to traffic between tourism
cities in the province and other provinces, according to the
governor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
