<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Polish Zloty 150 Million Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the launching of a Polish zloty
zero coupon indexed bond issue for the amount of PLN 150 million
under its Global Medium Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The Polish zloty bond issue which is approximately 47 million
U.S. dollars is IFC's second issue in the Euro Polish zloty
market. The two-year bonds were issued at a price of 70.75
percent.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be swapped into U.S. dollar
floating-rate funds.
</P>
<P>
The transaction brings IFC's market borrowings to about 3.7
billion dollars for the fiscal year 1997, which began on July 1,
1996.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
