<HEADLINE> British Stocks Hit Record for 7th Day in Row </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Major European stock markets
sustained their recent rally today, with both London and Frankfurt
hitting record closing highs and Paris surging more than 2
percent, supported by the Dow's strong rally.
</P>
<P>
The record-breaking run of the FTSE 100 index on the London
market continued today, buoyed by shock merger news in the UK and
another strong performance on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The index hit a seventh successive record close, rising 38.7
points or 0.84 percent to 4,669.6, having hit a day's low of 4,622
during earlier profit taking.
</P>
<P>
News of a planned 20 billion pound (32.5 billion US dollar)
merger between Britain's two drinks giants Grand Metropolitan and
Guinness sent both companies' shares soaring.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares came back from session highs, but
remained well supported as strong bonds offset the sharply weaker
dollar. The DAX-30 index finished the session up 12.96 points to
stand at 3,575.37, breaching the previous record closing high of
3,568.28 set last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, French shares tracked a positive showing
on Wall Street. Opinion polls showing a swing to the ruling
center-right parties in the upcoming election also boosted market
sentiment, with the CAC-40 index closing up 59.18 points at
2,693.09.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index of leading British shares ended up 38.7
points at 4,669.6. The Frankfurt DAX-30 index closed 12.96 points
higher at 3,575.37. In Paris, the CAC-40 index finished 59.18
points up at 2,693.09. 
</P>
