<HEADLINE> Dow Approaching 7,300 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
set a record today, almost touching the 7,300 mark, as investors
showed optimism about the outlook for inflation and interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow finished up 123.22 points to 7,293, beating last
Tuesday's record close by nearly 70 points.
</P>
<P>
The technology sector again saw big gains with IBM and
Hewlett-Packard leading the Dow industrials.
</P>
<P>
Investors have been expecting that economic data due later in
the week will further prove that the economy is easing enough to
keep inflation under control.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-3 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaled 459.01 million
shares as against 455.62 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 list rose 12.88 to 837.66, and the
NYSE composite index rose 6.34 to 435.57. Both measures set new
highs.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 9.14 to 1,344.19, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 4.69 to 578.47.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, stocks posted modest gains after fluctuating on
conflicting interpretations of a Thursday night speech by Alan
Greenspan, chairman of the Federal Reserve. 
</P>
