<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Reduces Embassy Staff in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The United States has reduced
its staff at the embassy in Kinshasa as Zairian rebel forces are
poised to attack the capital of Zaire, the State Department
said today.
</P>
<P>
It also said rumors are circulating that the Zairian government
forces would begin to attack expatriates as a way to draw foreign
troops into the fray.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the partial evacuation at a briefing, State
Department spokesman Nicholas Burns said the further reduction of
the staff came as "the situation is too precarious, too unstable
for them to stay."
</P>
<P>
Besides the uncertainty in the situation, Burns said, there
were rumors that the Zairian government forces had been ordered to
target expatriates in an attempt to trigger foreign military
intervention, which he said caused the most concern.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 12 Americans who departed went to neighboring Congo
by ferry or took flights to Europe or to other African capitals.
</P>
<P>
A total of 325 Americans who do not work for the U.S.
government remain in Zaire, down from about 400 a week ago.
</P>
<P>
Burns reaffirmed the State Department view that all such
Americans should leave the country as "the transfer of power is
going to happen one way or the other" with the rebel forces on the
march toward Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Navy Cmdr. Bob Anderson said Sunday that Americans began
finalizing their evacuation plans last week and U.S. soldiers and
helicopter gunships have been poised for weeks to evacuate them
from Zaire.
</P>
<P>
South Africa and the United States have so far unsuccessfully
attempted to broker a compromise between Zairian President Mobutu
Sese Seko and rebel leader Lauren Kabila over a proposed
transition period with resignation of the president, leading to
national elections.
</P>
<P>
Kabila has rejected the idea, insisting the power be handed
over directly to him. But he agreed to hold another meeting with
the president some days later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
